space On the Ground In Kuwait space Romanians Get "Perfect 10" for Decontamination Performance space A Romanian soldier cleans a container at the wash point at Port Shuaiba, Kuwait.
space space PORT SHUAIBA, Kuwait (July 21, 2003) -- Standing in formation in the morning Kuwaiti sun, about 40 Romanian soldiers from the 383rd NBC (nuclear, biological and chemical) Defense Company, Bistrita, Romania, accepted certificates from a very appreciative Col. Anthony D'Aquila, deputy chief of staff for the 143rd Transportation Command out of Orlando, Fla., for an outstanding job performing redeployment washing of more than 30,000 containers and vehicles.
The Romanian NBC unit arrived in theater on March 12, eight days before the start of Operation Iraqi Freedom.
The unit is part of the OIF Coalition to provide consequence management capabilities in response to a weapons of mass destruction attack, D'Aquila said.
"If the Iraqis had hit civilians with NBC-based Scud missiles, they would have been able to respond with their decontamination facilities," he added.
